LAFIA â€“ Honourable Murtala Lamus Special Adviser to Gov. Abdullahi Sule on Special Duties, has urged stakeholders and Executive members of All Progressives Congress (APC) in Wamba Local Government Area of Nasarawa to shun money bag politicians who are out to use delegates them and dump them. Hon Lamus made the call during an Expanded APC stakeholders and Executive members meeting of the Wamba Local Government Area of the State. He said money bag politicians would only use them for their selfish interests. The special adviser who applauded the achievements of Gov. Sule and Sen. Akwashiki said the two politicians have done a lot in their area, hence the need for stakeholders and delegates to give their overwhelming support to them to succeed. Hon Lamus moved a motion requesting a show of support from stakeholders which was seconded in a voice vote by APC Chairman, Wamba Local Government Area, Ibrahim Agyo and other executive members of the 10 electoral wards in the area. Lamus, who went through memory lane to outline the numerous achievements of both Gov. Sule and Sen. Akwashiki in the last few years in terms of infrastructural development among other gestures, also said that the projects embarked upon by the duo in the area have impacted positively on the lives of their people. The special adviser said that both Gov. Sule and Sen. Akwashiki are doing well in their respective offices. He explained that Wamba Local Government Area has benefitted from the duo in the area of construction of rural roads, healthcare centres and services as well as rehabilitation of primary and secondary schools among other developmental strides. POLL The Special Adviser also advised delegates to choose credible aspirants and to shun money-bag politicians, who will entice them with money during the party primaries scheduled for next month.